## Runtime Overlay

- This is the Codex-native thin overlay. Project truth lives in `ontology/`, `src/`, `tests/`, local `BROWSE.md` / `INDEX.md`, and generated verification outputs.
- `@palantirKC/claude-schemas` is pinned at `git+...#v1.0.0` in `package.json#peerDependencies`.
- When the shared home layer exists, import cross-project primitives through `~/ontology/shared-core` instead of importing `~/.claude/schemas/` directly from project code.
- `palantir-mini@1.0.0` is the baseline plugin surface: 10 MCP tools, 15 hooks, 6-phase validation, and L1/L2/L3 RBAC.
- `.claude/managed-settings.d/50-palantir-mini.json` is the per-project RBAC fragment.
- `.palantir-mini/session/events.jsonl` is append-only lineage. Never rewrite, reorder, or truncate it.
- `src/generated/` is codegen-owned. Regenerate rather than hand-edit.

## Working Order

- Start with local `BROWSE.md`, then local `INDEX.md`.
- Work `meaning -> ontology -> contracts -> runtime -> artifacts -> audit/learn`.
- Use installed palantir-mini workflows (`pm-init`, `pm-ontology-register`, `pm-codegen`, `pm-verify`) instead of project-local stubs.
